  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1 \u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d85\u0dad\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0dba\u0da7 \u0db4\u0ddc\u0daf\u0dd4 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A common term for foreign currency holders",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Central Bank has announced a general amnesty period for persons residing or residing in Sri Lanka who have foreign currency in their possession to attract that money into the banking system.",
        "This general amnesty is valid for one month from 15.08.2022. Accordingly, the respective amounts,",
        "i. To deposit into a personal foreign currency account or a business foreign currency account or",
        "ii. To sell to an authorized dealer (licensed commercial bank or national savings bank)."
      ],
